00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,880
[My Unicorn Girl]

3
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:18,640
[Episode 17, The "Guide Dog"
Gets a New Ability]

4
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:20,620
This is...

5
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:23,180
This is our new jersey.

6
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:24,900
New jersey!

7
00:01:25,260 --> 00:01:26,420
Do I look good in it?

8
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:27,780
Do I look good?

9
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,980
-Put it on.
-This looks awesome!

10
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,860
You look great!
It's good looking!

11
00:01:31,940 --> 00:01:32,979
That's right.

12
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:35,660
Look! Look at the design.
The logo is here.

13
00:01:35,860 --> 00:01:36,940
It suits you well.

14
00:01:39,509 --> 00:01:42,670
This is the first time the freshmen team
is taking part in a competition.

15
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,140
Mr. Class Monitor,

16
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:45,930
don't you have any wise words...

17
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:47,940
to say to everyone?

18
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:55,300
Gather around.
The class monitor has something to say.

19
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:56,500
Come.

20
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:00,820
Class monitor, please speak.

21
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:09,580
Thank you for your effort in training.

22
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:11,580
Especially Huang Hao Ran.

23
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,700
He has to focus on both
the training and his family.

24
00:02:13,780 --> 00:02:14,820
It's really not easy.

25
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:17,250
However, I would like to say...

26
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,660
whether it is a open tournament or not,

27
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,380
whether your friends and family
come to support you or not,

28
00:02:23,460 --> 00:02:24,540
it doesn't matter.

29
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:26,460
The most important thing is...

30
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,560
everyone is passionate about ice hockey.

31
00:02:38,770 --> 00:02:42,260
Even if no one can come and support us,

32
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:44,300
even if there is no audience,

33
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,860
we will have to do our best.

34
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,140
Enjoy the competition!

35
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,640
Well, let's do a team huddle!

36
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,420
All the best!

37
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,700
go for it

38
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:00,500
-All the best!
-Three, two, one!

39
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:01,860
All the best!

40
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:11,100
All the best!

41
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:12,900
All the best!

42
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:14,540
You are the best!

43
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:15,980
All the best, children!

44
00:03:17,510 --> 00:03:19,260
Fighting, son!

45
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:21,820
All the best, children!

46
00:03:21,980 --> 00:03:22,990
Dad!

47
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:27,270
All the best!

48
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:29,620
All the best!

49
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:30,940
All the best!

50
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:32,630
All the best, son!

51
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,620
All the best!

52
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,750
-Make me proud!
-All the best!

53
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:38,140
Wen Bing.

54
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,420
-All the best, son!
-Go get them!

55
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,460
I am here!

56
00:03:40,540 --> 00:03:42,220
-All the best!
-Your mum is proud of you!

57
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,570
I am here!

58
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,640
Why are their uniforms the same?

59
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:12,920
Meng Qi.

60
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,200
Get over here!

61
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:22,540
You better explain to me.

62
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:24,380
Where are their new jerseys?

63
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:28,700
[Captain.]

64
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:31,300
[These are new jerseys
Coach Ma got for the freshmen.]

65
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:34,720
[We should just give them
the spare jerseys.]

66
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:37,100
[It's just an intramural competition.]

67
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,880
[It shouldn't matter.]

68
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,680
You and your smart ideas.

69
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:44,420
How will they play if they wear
the same jerseys?

70
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,060
How would the referee and audience
tell them apart?

71
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:49,260
Coach, don't blame him.

72
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:50,300
It was my idea.

73
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:51,950
What I want is a solution.

74
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,159
Coach.

75
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,920
The competition is going to start soon.

76
00:04:57,980 --> 00:05:00,180
We won't make it if we tell everyone
to change their jerseys.

77
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:03,700
Why don't we stick numbers of
different colours at their back?

78
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:04,740
One black, one red.

79
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:06,140
It should be easy to differentiate.

80
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,820
We don't have a choice.

81
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,180
That's the only way.

82
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,580
[Wen Group]

83
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,240
[Furthermore,]

84
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,880
[if I take part in the competition,]

85
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:56,280
[you might come back to see me.]

86
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,160
[Do you know what is my
biggest obstacle right now?]

87
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,960
[It's you.]

88
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,720
[He knew about his love for ice hockey
since young.]

89
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,440
[If his passion...]

90
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,960
[is supported by his family,]

91
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,560
[he would be the happiest person
in the world.]

92
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:32,080
Chairman, we have an hour
until the Charity Reception begins.

93
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:33,640
It's time to depart.

94
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,159
[Alright, everyone.]

95
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:50,080
[The teams today are the freshmen team
and the senior team respectively.

96
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:55,080
[Who will win in the match?
The experienced or the budding students?]

97
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:57,159
[We shall wait and see.]

98
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,640
I had underestimated you
for the three on three match.

99
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,480
This time, I will make sure
I beat you fair and square.

100
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,880
Bring it on!

101
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:08,270
[It's easy to tell the difference
between black and red.]

102
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,120
[But the cards are on the back.]

103
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,720
[During head-to-head battle,]

104
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,700
[normal people recognise others
by looking at their faces.]

105
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:15,380
[However, for Wen Bing,]

106
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:17,220
[it's basically a disaster.]

107
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:20,600
[Alright, the match has officially begun.]

108
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:23,090
[A special thing about the match
is that both teams...]

109
00:07:23,170 --> 00:07:25,160
[are wearing the same jerseys.]

110
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:28,960
We shall wait and see which team
will stand out in the match.

111
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,120
[Freshman, Wen Bing,
has taken the first ball...]

112
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,920
[and passed it to Huang Hao Ran
at the back.]

113
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,280
[Huang Hao Ran passed the puck
 back to him.]

114
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,240
[As we can see,
Wen Bing is building up the attack.]

115
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,960
[He skates across the empty area.
breaks down the tight line of defense.]

116
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,400
[In lightning speed, he goes into the
attacking zone.]

117
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,960
[He is surrounded by the senior team.]

118
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,980
[Wen Bing, pass the puck!]

119
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,280
Pass the puck!

120
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,800
[Freshman, Wei Lian,
is knocking the ground.]

121
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,360
-Pass the puck, Wen Bing!
-[Signaling for him to pass.]

122
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,040
[Wen Bing passes the puck...]

123
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,320
[Wait...]

124
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:03,400
[Wen Bing, captain of the freshmen,
passed the puck to the opponent.]

125
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,440
[That is a huge mistake!]

126
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:12,580
Screw those jerseys.

127
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,580
They are purposely targeting Wen Bing.

128
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:29,030
Sister?

129
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,680
Sister!

130
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:33,620
It is you.

131
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,880
Didn't you say you wouldn't come
watch the match?

132
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,039
I am not here to watch the match.

133
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,159
The school council is conducting
a secret investigation.

134
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,600
I'm here for a covert observation.

135
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,680
Covert observation?

136
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:53,880
I think you look quite different
from usual.

137
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,360
Where is the red scarf that
you always wear?

138
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,240
That's none of your business.

139
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,480
What is this?

140
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,800
It's your birthday present.

141
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:12,080
You can adopt a cute puppy from
the pet shop with this card.

142
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,560
I'm good. I am allergic to dogs.

143
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,850
You are mentally allergic to dogs,
not physically. What's the fuss?

144
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:20,770
Furthermore, Bing Bing is away
for studies and you are all alone.

145
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,000
Your life is miserable!

146
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,720
-Why don't you adopt a puppy?
-Quiet.

147
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:31,040
[Huang Zhi Lie of the senior team passed
the ball to the captain, Meng Qi.]

148
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,760
[Freshman, Huang Hao Ran, tried
to stop them but to no avail.]

149
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,680
[Meng Qi is now in front of the goal.]

150
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,680
[Li He of the junior team immediately
approached them.]

151
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,740
[Meng Qi quickly shoots towards the goal.]

152
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,860
It's a goal!
The senior team leads by one!

153
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,880
Again.

154
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,800
All the best, everyone.

155
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,000
Keep at it!

156
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,000
You can do it!

157
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,800
Wen Bing, all the best!

158
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,000
You can do it!

159
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,080
Wen Bing.

160
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,480
Your mum is here.

161
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:09,730
She's there beside your uncle.

162
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,370
All the best!

163
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,320
All the best!

164
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:18,940
You can do it, Wen Bing!

165
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,360
All the best!

166
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,140
It's time.

167
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:25,100
All the best.

168
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,180
[The second period of the match
has begun.]

169
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:38,900
[The face off is once again between
the captains, Meng Qi and Wen Bing.]

170
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,500
[Wen Bing again has the first possession.]

171
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,600
[The players skate across
the midway in sync.]

172
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,400
[Wen Bing has control of the puck.]

173
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,560
Hurry, go, go!

174
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,840
[He moves forward!]

175
00:10:58,140 --> 00:11:01,260
[Zhang Kai Wen knocked Wen Bing off to the
side of the rink. He lost the puck.]

176
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,440
[Meng Qi and the gang passed the puck
to the attacking zone.]

177
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,360
[They have initiated
the defensive counterattack.]

178
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:11,980
It's okay.

179
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,800
Look at the referee.

180
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,720
Is he blind? Look at him.

181
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,480
He didn't stop them despite the foul.

182
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:21,120
-Is he a mascot?
-You are so noisy.

183
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,560
Will you keep quiet?

184
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,040
[The puck is in Meng Qi's possession.]

185
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,400
[He breaks through the heavy siege...]

186
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,760
[and is skating towards
the junior goalie, Xiao Xiao.]

187
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:34,500
[He shoots!]

188
00:11:34,580 --> 00:11:35,800
[Well done! Another goal!]

189
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,480
[The senior team scores another point.]

190
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:45,540
[The performance of the freshmen team
is awful,]

191
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:47,080
[especially their captain, Wen Bing.]

192
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:49,280
[He can definitely play better.]

193
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:51,060
[He is not in his best form.]

194
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:59,060
Wen Bing, don't give up.

195
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,120
We still have time.

196
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,720
Wen Bing.

197
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:09,800
I suggest that you consider
changing members.

198
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,000
Coach Ma.

199
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,360
I still can play.

200
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,240
You are not in your best form today.

201
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,120
If you continue playing,
the team will lose even harder.

202
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,240
Coach Ma.

203
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:46,840
As the vice monitor, I plead to you
not to change out Wen Bing.

204
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:49,990
This is the debut match
for the freshmen team.

205
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:52,860
Everyone including the teachers, students
and parents are watching.

206
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,060
Think carefully.

207
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:55,860
Don't be blinded by emotions.

208
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:00,360
I have made up my mind.

209
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,880
We're not switching players.

210
00:13:02,060 --> 00:13:03,560
Whatever happens,

211
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,280
I shall be held solely responsible.

212
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,880
You said we should do our best...

213
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,480
and enjoy the match, right?

214
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,840
So why are you leaving?

215
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,200
I have tried my best.

216
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:11,220
I leave the rest to you guys.

217
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:13,780
You are the captain.

218
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,620
You must not leave the rink.

219
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,880
Coach Ma is right.

220
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:22,520
I am not in my best form to keep playing.

221
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:25,400
Plus, my mum is in the audience.

222
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,500
I don't want her to see me fail.

223
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,680
That would confirm everything
she said before.

224
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,640
I bet now...

225
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,600
she is even more certain that
ice hockey is not for me.

226
00:15:02,030 --> 00:15:03,420
You are meant to play ice hockey.

227
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,180
Trust me.

228
00:15:05,590 --> 00:15:08,670
You are the most talented
ice hockey player that I have ever seen.

229
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:16,110
I'm asking you as the vice monitor...

230
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:19,070
to play your best
in the last two periods of the match.

231
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:20,510
You can do it.

232
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:24,830
Do your best!

233
00:15:24,910 --> 00:15:26,230
Don't disappoint your mum.

234
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:47,100
All the best.

235
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,270
[The match continues.]

236
00:17:00,350 --> 00:17:02,960
[The freshmen team, led by Wen Bing,]

237
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:05,670
[is up against the senior team,
led by Meng Qi.]

238
00:17:06,069 --> 00:17:08,550
[The current score is zero to two.]

239
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:11,470
[Things are not looking good
for the freshmen.]

240
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:14,430
[It seems that experience
cannot be ignored.]

241
00:17:18,619 --> 00:17:21,099
[Sang Tian received the puck
from Shen Wei Lian.]

242
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:29,150
[Sang Tian passed the puck
at a very challenging angle.]

243
00:17:29,230 --> 00:17:30,570
[Wen Bing accelerates.]

244
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:34,140
[Meng Qi is following closely
to try stop him.]

245
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:37,590
[Nice! Wen Bing received the puck!]

246
00:17:37,670 --> 00:17:40,590
[His performance is different
from before.]

247
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,190
[He makes a rapid breakthrough.]

248
00:17:43,670 --> 00:17:45,790
[He passed the puck to Wei Lian
who is at the side.]

249
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:48,910
[Will he receive the puck?]

250
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:51,230
[Shen Wei Lian swings the stick,
preparing to shoot.]

251
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,960
[It's a goal! A tricky one to boot.]

252
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:58,420
[Amazing! The passing of the puck
was so smooth!]

253
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,580
Good one!

254
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:02,060
Finally the junior team has scored
their first point.

255
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,100
All the best!

256
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:06,500
It seems that the freshmen team
is slowly finding their form.

257
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:07,960
Nice!

258
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:09,030
Well done!

259
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:10,190
Keep it up!

260
00:18:13,190 --> 00:18:14,390
Keep it up!

261
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:19,850
We can do it!

262
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:25,130
[Ice hockey friendly match,
seniors versus freshmen]

263
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:27,510
[We have one minute to go.
The match is getting more intense.]

264
00:18:27,790 --> 00:18:29,390
